headline: Southwest’s Starlink WiFi and Cabin Overhaul Might Change The Case For Investing In Southwest Airlines (LUV)
summary: Southwest Airlines recently announced it is rolling out SpaceX’s Starlink high-speed inflight WiFi across its 11-country network, starting with the first equipped aircraft this summer and targeting more than 300 aircraft by the end of 2026 as part of a broader cabin upgrade program. The move to pair free, next-generation WiFi for loyalty members with new assigned and premium seating, extra-legroom rows, and in-seat power signals a shift toward a more segmented, higher-service product that...

headline: Can American Airlines turn itself around?
summary: American Airlines has promised Wall Street and travelers that 2026 will be a turnaround year. It’s been trailing its U.S. competitors Delta Air Lines and United Airlines in profits and reliability by a wide margin and has fallen behind in the race for premium air travel. So the pressure is on for CEO Robert Isom.
